insurancetimes.co.uk/expert-views)\n\n  + [Without authenticity, straight through processing has a major problem – Truepic](/expert-views/without-authenticity-straight-through-processing-has-a-major-problem-truepic/1458167.article)\n  + [How CMA reforms could impact pet insurance pricing – Pearson Ham](/expert-views/how-cma-reforms-could-impact-pet-insurance-pricing-pearson-ham/1458166.article)\n  + [Building a career in insurance and the value of staying power – HDI Global](/expert-views/building-a-career-in-insurance-and-the-value-of-staying-power-hdi-global/1457557.article)\n  + [Laying down the law – Arag](/expert-views/laying-down-the-law-arag/1457556.article)\n* [Edition](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/edition)\n* [More navigation items](#mobilemenu)\n\n[News](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news)\n\n# Saga boosts profit in 2025 after Ageas deal\n\nBy [George McDade](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/george-mcdade/2313.bio)2026-04-15T13:00:00+01:00\n\n* [No comments](#commentsJump)\n\n‘The restructuring of our insurance business, and the partnership with Ageas, derisks and simplifies our operating model, creating a more stable platform for growth,’ says group chief executive\n\n[Saga](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/saga-news/20574.more?navcode=4300) has announced improved revenue and profit levels in its latest full year preliminary [financial results](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/topics/financial-/-results), released today (15 April 2026).\n\n**Read: [Policy Expert posts strong results ‘despite a challenging insurance market’](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/policy-expert-posts-strong-results-despite-a-challenging-insurance-market/1458131.article)**\n\n**Read: [Allianz posts 30% increased operating profit in UK for FY 2025 results](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/allianz-posts-30-increased-operating-profit-in-uk-for-fy-2025-results/1457875.article)**\n\nNot subscribed? [Become a subscriber and access our premium content](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/subscriptions)\n\n[**Explore more**](https://account.insurancetimes.co.uk/subscribe?sourcecode=ITStandard18&campaigncode=ITSUBIA&returl=https%3a%2f%2fwww.insurancetimes.co.uk)**[financial-related content here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/topics/financial), or discover other [news content here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news)**\n\nSaga said its results – covering the full year to 31 January 2026 – were underpinned by strong performances in both its travel and insurance businesses.\n\nThe firm specialises in providing products and services to the over 50s, including car, home and travel insurance, as well as non-insurance products such as travel and holidays and financial services.\n\nRevenue grew by 12% between years – up from £588m in 2024 to £660m in 2025 – while profit before tax rose to £2.1m for the year, up from a loss of £160m in 2024.\n\nThe results come after the sale of the firm’s insurance underwriting business to [Ageas](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/ageas-news/20264.more?navcode=4267), which Saga said removed “all underwriting risk from the group” and reduced “complexity and volatility”.\n\nThe firm also launched a motor and home insurance partnership with Ageas as part of a plan to simplify its insurance broking operations.\n\n### Stable platform\n\nMike Hazell, group chief executive at Saga, said: “This has been a transformational year for Saga. The restructuring of our insurance business, and the partnership with Ageas, derisks and simplifies our operating model, creating a more stable platform for growth.\n\n**Read: [HDI Global sees insurance revenue climb 5% in latest results](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/hdi-global-sees-insurance-revenue-climb-5-in-latest-results/1458093.article)**\n\n**Read: [Hiscox plans raft of new product launches for 2025’s H2](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/hiscox-plans-raft-of-new-product-launches-for-2025s-h2/1456024.article)**\n\n**Explore more [financial results content here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/topics/financial-/-results), or discover other [news stories here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news)**\n\n“The result was an excellent trading performance that drove growth across all our core businesses and a strong financial performance, with underlying profit before tax and the leverage ratio significantly ahead of our original guidance.”\n\nHe continued: “As we look ahead, our performance this year has further strengthened the confidence we have in our medium-term targets of delivering underlying profits of at least £100m by January 2030 and leverage below 2.0x.\n\n“We will deliver this by focussing on Saga’s core strengths and the 75 years of experience we have in designing, marketing and delivering products and services for people over 50.”\n\n[George McDade](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/george-mcdade/2313.bio)\n\n* Follow\n\nGeorge is a data reporter at Insurance Times, uncovering interesting industry trends and reporting on the technological advancements that will shape the future of the sector.  \n  \nHe graduated in 2017 from the University of Manchester with a degree in Geology. He spent the first part of his career working in consulting and tech, spending time at Citibank as a data analyst, before working as an analytics engineer with clients in the retail, technology, manufacturing and financial services sectors.[View full Profile](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/george-mcdade/2313.bio)\n\n## [More George McDade](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/george-mcdade/2313.bio)\n\n* ## [Specialty insurer expands London market energy and power capabilities](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/specialty-insurer-expands-london-market-energy-and-power-capabilities/1458283.article)\n* ## [Motor brokers turn tide on customer losses to insurers](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/analysis/motor-brokers-turn-tide-on-customer-losses-to-insurers/1458220.article)\n* ## [Profits climb for Covéa despite GWP drop](https://www.insuran