2313.bio)2026-04-14T13:00:00+01:00\n\n* [No comments](#commentsJump)\n\n‘This performance reflects a business that is operating with greater financial discipline and balance sheet strength,’ says chairman\n\n[Covéa](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/covea-news/20408.more?navcode=4285) Insurance has posted improved profits in its 2025 full year financial [results](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/topics/financial-/-results), despite a dip in gross written premium (GWP).\n\n**Read: [Policy Expert posts strong results ‘despite a challenging insurance market’](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/policy-expert-posts-strong-results-despite-a-challenging-insurance-market/1458131.article)**\n\n**Read: [Allianz posts 30% increased operating profit in UK for FY 2025 results](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/allianz-posts-30-increased-operating-profit-in-uk-for-fy-2025-results/1457875.article)**\n\nNot subscribed? [Become a subscriber and access our premium content](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/subscriptions)\n\n[**Explore more**](https://account.insurancetimes.co.uk/subscribe?sourcecode=ITStandard18&campaigncode=ITSUBIA&returl=https%3a%2f%2fwww.insurancetimes.co.uk)**[financial-related content here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/topics/financial), or discover other [news content here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news)**\n\nThe results – released today (14 April 2026) – revealed that the firm’s profit before tax more than doubled between years, up from £32.9m in 2024 to £72.4m in 2025.\n\nThis came despite a GWP fall, with the firm’s £616.8m posting for the current year some 3.85% lower than the £641.5m seen in 2024.\n\nThe firm’s combined operating ratio (COR) also improved, dropping from 97.8% to 91.6% between periods.\n\n### Financial performance\n\nPhilippe Domart, chief executive at Covéa Insurance, said: “2025 was an excellent year for Covéa Insurance, not only in terms of financial performance but in the strength and confidence of the organisation.\n\n**Read: [HDI Global sees insurance revenue climb 5% in latest results](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/hdi-global-sees-insurance-revenue-climb-5-in-latest-results/1458093.article)**\n\n**Read: [Hiscox plans raft of new product launches for 2025’s H2](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news/hiscox-plans-raft-of-new-product-launches-for-2025s-h2/1456024.article)**\n\n**Explore more [financial results content here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/topics/financial-/-results), or discover other [news stories here](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/news)**\n\n“Building on a profitable 2024, the strong performance in 2025 validates the business strategy, proves the resilience of the organisation and its ability to execute well, with discipline and pace.\n\n“The teams can rightly feel proud of their collective achievements, energised for the future, driven to deliver best-in-class service to our [brokers](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/brokers) and clients and continue to earn their trust amid a demanding and evolving market.”\n\nChris Moat, chairman of Covéa’s board of directors, added: “This performance reflects a business that is operating with greater financial discipline and balance sheet strength.\n\n“Our capital position remains robust, underwriting performance has continued to improve and we are benefiting from a more stable and resilient operating model. This places us in a strong position to support brokers consistently and sustainably over the long-term.”\n\n[George McDade](https://www.insurancetimes.co.uk/george-mcdade/2313.bio)\n\n* Follow\n\nGeorge is a data reporter at Insurance Times, uncovering interesting industry trends and reporting on the technological advancements that will shape the future of the sector.  \n  \nHe graduated in 2017 from the University of Manchester with a degree in Geology. He spent the first part of his career working in consulting and tech, spending time at Citibank as a data analyst, before working as an analytics engineer wi